Key Match Events: Netherlands 158 for 4 (Ackermann 41*, Myburgh 37, Cooper 35, Maharaj 2-27) beat South Africa 145 for 8 (Rossouw 25, Glover 3-9, Klaassen 2-20, de Leede 2-25) by 13 runs
Roelof van der Merwe's incredible catch to dismiss David Miller
Stephan Myburgh's aggressive batting at the start
Colin Ackermann's finishing with 41 not out off 26
Post-Match Reflections: Netherlands celebrated a seminal moment in their cricket history
South Africa faced heartbreak and despondency after the loss
The result guaranteed India a spot in the semi-finals
The Bangladesh vs Pakistan match became a knockout contest due to Netherlands' win
Miscellaneous Highlights: The win could mean a top-four finish in the group for Netherlands, guaranteeing them an automatic qualification for the next T20 World Cup
